docs.lead_paragraph: The Republican pollster who had planned to split time advising both Vice President Mike Pence and the United Nations ambassador, Nikki R. Haley, on national security issues withdrew from the dual role on Sunday night, a White House official said.

docs.abstract: President Trump lashed out at Senator Jon Tester, the Democrat who helped thwart the cabinet nomination of Dr. Ronny L. Jackson.
docs.snippet: President Trump lashed out at Senator Jon Tester, the Democrat who helped thwart the cabinet nomination of Dr. Ronny L. Jackson.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump called on Saturday for the resignation of Senator Jon Tester and threatened to spread allegations about the Democratic lawmaker in retaliation for helping to thwart his effort to install the White House physician in the cabinet.

headline.main: Trump Calls on Montana Democrat to Resign in Fight Over Failed V.A. Nomination

docs.abstract: Mr. Bolton takes over as the president’s third national security adviser Monday. In a world of carrot-and-stick diplomacy, Mr. Bolton is a stick man: “I don’t do carrots.”

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Shortly after Ambassador John R. Bolton was sent to represent the United States at the United Nations, an institution he had long scorned as an anti-American citadel of corruption, he hosted President George W. Bush for a visit.

headline.main: In John Bolton, Trump Finds a Fellow Political Blowtorch. Will Foreign Policy Burn?

docs.abstract: The peculiar, painful limbo of David Shulkin shows how the president often handles personnel matters: publicly, hoping the employee will leave instead of forcing an ouster.
docs.snippet: The peculiar, painful limbo of David Shulkin shows how the president often handles personnel matters: publicly, hoping the employee will leave instead of forcing an ouster.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump wants to replace his secretary of veterans affairs, David Shulkin, but for a man who practically trademarked “You’re fired,” the president is reluctant to pull the trigger, choosing instead to leave the embattled secretary twisting amid reports of his imminent ouster.

headline.main: Trump, Famous for ‘You’re Fired,’ Offers V.A. Chief Only Awkward Silence
headline.print_headline: Awkward Silence on V.A. Chief From Man With Catchphrase of ‘You’re Fired’

docs.abstract: Charles Rettig is expected to be confirmed to lead a department that has been a political punching bag.
docs.snippet: Charles Rettig is expected to be confirmed to lead a department that has been a political punching bag.
docs.lead_paragraph: President Trump’s pick to lead the Internal Revenue Service, Charles Rettig, said on Thursday that he would make it a priority to run the department without bias, an attempt to ease lawmakers’ concerns that the tax collection agency could be weaponized for political purposes.

headline.main: I.R.S. Nominee Says He Won’t Weaponize Agency
headline.print_headline: I.R.S. Pick Pledges to Remain Impartial

docs.abstract: Hundreds of companies were hurt by the Trump tax cuts, which failed to extend dozens of expiring tax credits. Executives at Plug Power never lost hope.
docs.snippet: Hundreds of companies were hurt by the Trump tax cuts, which failed to extend dozens of expiring tax credits. Executives at Plug Power never lost hope.
docs.lead_paragraph: LATHAM, N.Y. — By noon on Wednesday, the snow was ankle-deep in the parking lot and the workers had abandoned the factory floor at Plug Power to escape the storm. Hydrogen-powered fuel cells meant for forklifts in Amazon or Walmart warehouses sat half-finished in steel casings.

headline.main: The Trump Tax Cuts Hurt This Manufacturer. It Kept On Lobbying.
headline.print_headline: When Your Fate Hinges on a Tax Bill

docs.abstract: Education Secretary Betsy DeVos, frustrated by congressional inaction, is preparing an overhaul of the law governing the nation’s 4,000 colleges and universities.
docs.snippet: Education Secretary Betsy DeVos, frustrated by congressional inaction, is preparing an overhaul of the law governing the nation’s 4,000 colleges and universities.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The top Republican on the Senate Education Committee effectively killed on Thursday all hope for a highly anticipated overhaul this year of the law governing the nation’s 4,000 colleges and universities, paving the way for Education Secretary Betsy DeVos to wield her deregulatory power.

headline.main: With Legislation Stalled, DeVos Moves to Wield Deregulatory Power
headline.print_headline: DeVos, Tired of Stalled Congress, Is Clearing a Path for Changes

docs.abstract: Justice’s Antitrust Division is looking into the way colleges and universities use the early decision application process, possibly with an eye on collusion.
docs.snippet: Justice’s Antitrust Division is looking into the way colleges and universities use the early decision application process, possibly with an eye on collusion.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Justice Department is probing whether colleges and universities are violating antitrust laws by exchanging information about prospective students who make early decision commitments, the latest in a series of higher education-admissions policies that prosecutors are scrutinizing.

headline.main: Justice Department Launches Probe of College Early Admissions
headline.print_headline: Justice Dept. Investigates Early College Admissions

docs.abstract: President Trump demanded to know at a White House meeting why he should accept immigrants from Haiti and African countries rather than people from places like Norway.
docs.snippet: President Trump demanded to know at a White House meeting why he should accept immigrants from Haiti and African countries rather than people from places like Norway.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump on Thursday balked at an immigration deal that would include protections for people from Haiti and some nations in Africa, demanding to know at a White House meeting why he should accept immigrants from “shithole countries” rather than from places like Norway, according to people with direct knowledge of the conversation.

headline.main: Trump Alarms Lawmakers With Disparaging Words for Haiti and Africa
headline.print_headline: In Vulgar Terms, Trump Disparages Some Immigrants

docs.abstract: The case was the latest battle in a partisan war over how far states can go in imposing all kinds of voting restrictions, including cutbacks on early voting and tough voter ID laws.
docs.snippet: The case was the latest battle in a partisan war over how far states can go in imposing all kinds of voting restrictions, including cutbacks on early voting and tough voter ID laws.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Supreme Court on Monday upheld Ohio’s aggressive efforts to purge its voting rolls, siding with Republicans in the latest partisan battle over how far states can go in imposing restrictions on voting.

headline.main: Supreme Court Upholds Ohio’s Purge of Voting Rolls
headline.print_headline: Supreme Court Upholds Purge Of Ohio Voters
